{"label": 0, "text": "Gratified, Ven."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Rahula delighted in the Blessed One's words."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Once the Blessed One was staying at Kosambi in the Simsapa tree grove."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Then, picking up a few Simsapa leaves with his hand, he asked the monks, What do you think, monks Which are more numerous, the few Simsapa leaves in my hand or those overhead in the Simsapa grove?The leaves in the hand of the Blessed One are few in number, lord."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Those overhead in the grove are far more numerous.In the same way, monks, those things that I have known with direct knowledge but have not taught are far more numerous than the things I have taught."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And why haven't I taught them?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because they are not connected with the goal, do not relate to the rudiments of the holy life, and do not lead to disenchantment, to dispassion, to cessation, to calm, to direct knowledge, to self-awakening, to Unbinding."}
{"label": 0, "text": "That is why I have not taught them.And what have I taught?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "'This is stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the origination of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the cessation of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress.' This is what I have taught."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And why have I taught these things?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because they are connected with the goal, relate to the rudiments of the holy life, and lead to disenchantment, to dispassion, to cessation, to calm, to direct knowledge, to self-awakening, to Unbinding."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is why I have taught them.Therefore your duty is the contemplation, 'This is stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the origination of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the cessation of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress.'"}
{"label": 0, "text": "'Stress should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The cause by which stress comes into play should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The diversity in stress should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The result of stress should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The cessation of stress should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The path of practice for the cessation of stress should be known.' Thus it has been said."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Why was it said?Birth is stressful, aging is stressful, death is stressful; sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair are stressful; association with what is not loved is stressful, separation from what is loved is stressful, not getting what is wanted is stressful."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In short, the five clinging-aggregates are stressful.And what is the cause by which stress comes into play?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Craving is the cause by which stress comes into play.And what is the diversity in stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is major stress & minor, slowly fading & quickly fading."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called the diversity in stress.And what is the result of stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There are some cases in which a person overcome with pain, his mind exhausted, grieves, mourns, laments, beats his breast, & becomes bewildered."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Or one overcome with pain, his mind exhausted, comes to search outside, 'Who knows a way or two to stop this pain?' I tell you, monks, that stress results either in bewilderment or in search.And what is the cessation of stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The cessation of craving is the cessation of stress, and just this noble eightfold path is the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress right view, right resolve, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right concentration.Now when a disciple of the noble ones discerns stress in this way, the cause by which stress comes into play in this way, the diversity of stress in this way, the result of stress in this way, the cessation of stress in this way, & the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress in this way, then he discerns this penetrative holy life as the cessation of stress.'Stress should be known."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The cause by which stress comes into play."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The variations in stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The result of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The cessation of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The path of practice for the cessation of stress should be experienced.' Thus it has been said, and this is why it was said."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Vision arose, clear knowing arose, discernment arose, knowledge arose, illumination arose within me with regard to things never heard before 'This is the noble truth of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of stress is to be comprehended."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of stress has been comprehended."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the noble truth of the origination of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the origination of stress is to be abandoned."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the origination of stress has been abandoned."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the noble truth of the cessation of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the cessation of stress is to be realized."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the cessation of stress has been realized."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the noble truth of the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress is to be developed."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This noble truth of the path of practice leading to the cessation of stress has been developed.'And, monks, as long as this knowledge & vision of mine  with its three rounds & twelve permutations concerning these four noble truths as they actually are  was not pure, I did not claim to have directly awakened to the unexcelled right self-awakening."}
{"label": 0, "text": "But as soon as this knowledge & vision of mine  with its three rounds & twelve permutations concerning these four noble truths as they actually are  was truly pure, only then did I claim to have directly awakened to the unexcelled right self-awakening."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The knowledge & vision arose in me 'Unprovoked is my release."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the last birth."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is now no further becoming.'was"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Sariputta There are these three forms of stressfulness, my friend the stressfulness of pain, the stressfulness of fabrication, the stressfulness of change."}
{"label": 0, "text": "These are the three forms of stressfulness.Sariputta"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Sariputta Now what, friends, is the noble truth of stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Birth is stressful, aging is stressful, death is stressful; sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair are stressful; not getting what is wanted is stressful."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In short, the five clinging-aggregates are stressful.SariputtaNow what is birth?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever birth, taking birth, descent, coming-to-be, coming-forth, appearance of aggregates, & acquisition of sense media of the various beings in this or that group of beings, that is called birth.birth?And what is aging?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever aging, decrepitude, brokenness, graying, wrinkling, decline of life-force, weakening of the faculties of the various beings in this or that group of beings, that is called aging.aging?And what is death?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever deceasing, passing away, breaking up, disappearance, dying, death, completion of time, break up of the aggregates, casting off of the body, interruption in the life faculty of the various beings in this or that group of beings, that is called death.death?And what is sorrow?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever sorrow, sorrowing, sadness, inward sorrow, inward sadness of anyone suffering from misfortune, touched by a painful thing, that is called sorrow.sorrow?And what is lamentation?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever crying, grieving, lamenting, weeping, wailing, lamentation of anyone suffering from misfortune, touched by a painful thing, that is called lamentation.lamentation?And what is pain?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever is experienced as bodily pain, bodily discomfort, pain or discomfort born of bodily contact, that is called pain.pain?And what is distress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever is experienced as mental pain, mental discomfort, pain or discomfort born of mental contact, that is called distress.distress?And what is despair?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever despair, despondency, desperation of anyone suffering from misfortune, touched by a painful thing, that is called despair.despair?And what is the stress of not getting what one wants?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "In beings subject to birth, the wish arises, 'O, may we not be subject to birth, and may birth not come to us.' But this is not to be achieved by wishing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the stress of not getting what one wants."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In beings subject to aging."}
{"label": 0, "text": "illness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "death."}
{"label": 0, "text": "sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair, the wish arises, 'O, may we not be subject to aging."}
{"label": 0, "text": "illness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "death."}
{"label": 0, "text": "sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair, and may aging."}
{"label": 0, "text": "illness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "death."}
{"label": 0, "text": "sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair not come to us.' But this is not to be achieved by wishing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the stress of not getting what one wants.And what are the five clinging-aggregates that, in short, are stressful?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Form as a clinging-aggregate, feeling as a clinging-aggregate, perception as a clinging-aggregate, fabrications as a clinging-aggregate, consciousness as a clinging-aggregate These are called the five clinging-aggregates that, in short, are stressful.This is called the noble truth of stress."}
{"label": 0, "text": "At Savatthi."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There the Blessed One said, Monks, I will teach you the five aggregates & the five clinging-aggregates."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Listen & pay close attention."}
{"label": 0, "text": "I will speak.As you say, lord, the monks responded.The Blessed One said, Now what, monks, are the five aggregates?Whatever form is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near that is called the form aggregate.Whatever feeling is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near that is called the feeling aggregate.Whatever perception is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near that is called the perception aggregate.Whatever (mental) fabrications are past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near those are called the fabrication aggregate.Whatever consciousness is past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near that is called the consciousness aggregate.These are called the five aggregates.And what are the five clinging-aggregates?Whatever form  past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near  is clingable, offers sustenance, and is accompanied with mental fermentation that is called form as clinging-aggregate.Whatever feeling  past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near  is clingable, offers sustenance, and is accompanied with mental fermentation that is called feeling as a clinging-aggregate.Whatever perception  past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near  is clingable, offers sustenance, and is accompanied with mental fermentation that is called perception as a clinging-aggregate.Whatever (mental) fabrications  past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near  are clingable, offer sustenance, and are accompanied with mental fermentation those are called fabrication as a clinging-aggregate.Whatever consciousness  past, future, or present; internal or external; blatant or subtle; common or sublime; far or near  is clingable, offers sustenance, and is accompanied with mental fermentation that is called consciousness as a clinging-aggregate.These are called the five clinging-aggregates."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The Buddha These are the five clinging-aggregates form as a clinging-aggregate, feeling as a clinging-aggregate, perception as a clinging-aggregate, fabrications as a clinging-aggregate, consciousness as a clinging-aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "These five clinging-aggregates are rooted in desire.The BuddhaA certain monk Is it the case that clinging and the five clinging-aggregates are the same thing, or are they separate?A certain monkThe Buddha Clinging is neither the same thing as the five clinging-aggregates, nor are they separate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever desire & passion there is with regard to the five clinging-aggregates, that is the clinging there.The BuddhaThe monk What is the cause, what is the condition, for the discernibility of the form aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "feeling aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "perception aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "fabrications aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "consciousness aggregate?The monkThe Buddha The four great existents [the properties of earth, water, fire, & wind] are the cause & condition for the discernibility of the form aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Contact is the cause & condition for the discernibility of the feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "perception."}
{"label": 0, "text": "fabrications aggregate."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Name & form are the cause & condition for the discernibility of the consciousness aggregate.The Buddha"}
{"label": 0, "text": "And why do you call it 'form' (rupa)?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it is afflicted (ruppati), thus it is called 'form.' Afflicted with what?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "With cold & heat & hunger & thirst, with the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, & reptiles."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it is afflicted, it is called form.(rupa)?(ruppati),And why do you call it 'feeling'?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it feels, thus it is called 'feeling.' What does it feel?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "It feels pleasure, it feels pain, it feels neither-pleasure-nor-pain."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it feels, it is called feeling.And why do you call it 'perception'?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it perceives, thus it is called 'perception.' What does it perceive?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "It perceives blue, it perceives yellow, it perceives red, it perceives white."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it perceives, it is called perception.And why do you call them 'fabrications'?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because they fabricate fabricated things, thus they are called 'fabrications.' What do they fabricate as a fabricated thing?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "From form-ness, they fabricate form as a fabricated thing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From feeling-ness, they fabricate feeling as a fabricated thing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From perception-hood.From fabrication-hood.From consciousness-hood, they fabricate consciousness as a fabricated thing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because they fabricate fabricated things, they are called fabrications.And why do you call it 'consciousness'?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it cognizes, thus it is called consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What does it cognize?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "It cognizes what is sour, bitter, pungent, sweet, alkaline, non-alkaline, salty, & unsalty."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Because it cognizes, it is called consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "MahaKotthita Feeling, perception, & consciousness are these qualities conjoined or disjoined?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "And is it possible, having divided them, to describe their separateness?MahaKotthitaSariputta Feeling, perception, & consciousness are conjoined, not disjoined, and it is impossible, having divided them, to describe their separateness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "For what one feels, that one perceives; and what one perceives, that one cognizes."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Form.Sariputta And what, friends, is form as a clinging-aggregate?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The four great existents and the form derived from them."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what are the four great existents?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "They are the earth-property, the water property, the fire property, & the wind property.SariputtaAnd what is the earth property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The earth property may be either internal or external."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What is the internal earth property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever internal, belonging to oneself, is solid, solidified, & sustained head hairs, body hairs, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, tendons, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, pleura, spleen, lungs, large intestines, small intestines, contents of the stomach, feces, or whatever else internally, belonging to oneself, is solid, solidified, & sustained This is called the internal earth property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now both the internal earth property and the external earth property are simply earth property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment 'This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self.' When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the earth property and makes the earth property fade from the mind.And what is the water property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The water property may be either internal or external."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What is the internal water property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever internal, belonging to oneself, is liquid, watery, & sustained bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, skin-oil, saliva, mucus, oil-of-the-joints, urine, or whatever else internally, belonging to oneself, is liquid, watery, & sustained This is called the internal water property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now both the internal water property and the external water property are simply water property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment 'This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self.' When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the water property and makes the water property fade from the mind.And what is the fire property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The fire property may be either internal or external."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What is the internal fire property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever internal, belonging to oneself, is fire, fiery, & sustained that by which one is warmed, ages, & wastes away; and that by which what is eaten, drunk, consumed, & tasted gets completely digested, or whatever else internally, belonging to oneself, is fire, fiery, & sustained This is called the internal fire property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now both the internal fire property and the external fire property are simply fire property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment 'This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self.' When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the fire property and makes the fire property fade from the mind.And what is the wind property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The wind property may be either internal or external."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What is the internal wind property?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever internal, belonging to oneself, is wind, windy, & sustained up-going winds, down-going winds, winds in the stomach, winds in the intestines, winds that course through the body, in-&-out breathing, or whatever else internally, belonging to oneself, is wind, windy, & sustained This is called the internal wind property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now both the internal wind property and the external wind property are simply wind property."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And that should be seen as it actually is present with right discernment 'This is not mine, this is not me, this is not my self.' When one sees it thus as it actually is present with right discernment, one becomes disenchanted with the wind property and makes the wind property fade from the mind."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Feeling.Sister Dhammadinna There are three kinds of feeling pleasant feeling, painful feeling, & neither-pleasant-nor-painful feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever is experienced physically or mentally as pleasant & gratifying is pleasant feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever is experienced physically or mentally as painful & hurting is painful feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Whatever is experienced physically or mentally as neither gratifying nor hurting is neither-pleasant-nor-painful feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Pleasant feeling is pleasant in remaining and painful in changing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Painful feeling is painful in remaining and pleasant in changing."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Neither-pleasant-nor-painful feeling is pleasant when conjoined with knowledge and painful when devoid of knowledge.Sister Dhammadinna"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Fabrications.And what are fabrications?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There are these six classes of intention intention aimed at sights, sounds, aromas, tastes, tactile sensations, & ideas."}
{"label": 0, "text": "These are called fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Sister Dhammadinna In-&-out breathing is bodily, bound up with the body, therefore is it called a bodily fabrication."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Having directed one's thought and evaluated [the matter], one breaks into speech."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Therefore directed thought & evaluation are called verbal fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Perception & feeling are mental, bound up with the mind."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Therefore perception & feeling are called mental fabrications.Sister Dhammadinnabodily fabrication.verbal fabrications.mental fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Consciousness.Consciousness is classified simply by the condition in dependence on which it arises.When consciousness arises in dependence on eye & forms, it is classified simply as eye-consciousness.When consciousness arises in dependence on ear & sounds, it is classified simply as ear-consciousness.When consciousness arises in dependence on nose & smells, it is classified simply as nose-consciousness.When consciousness arises in dependence on tongue & tastes, it is classified simply as tongue-consciousness.When consciousness arises in dependence on body & tactile sensations, it is classified simply as body-consciousness.When consciousness arises in dependence on intellect & ideas, it is classified simply as intellect-consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now what is the noble truth of the origination of stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The craving that makes for further becoming  accompanied by passion & delight, relishing now here & now there  i.e., craving for sensuality, craving for becoming, craving for non-becoming."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what is the noble truth of the cessation of stress?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The remainderless fading & cessation, renunciation, relinquishment, release, & letting go of that very craving."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what is the noble method that is rightly seen & rightly ferreted out by discernment?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is the case where a disciple of the noble ones notices When this is, that is."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the arising of this comes the arising of that."}
{"label": 0, "text": "When this isn't, that isn't."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of this comes the cessation of that."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With ignorance as a condition there are fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With fabrications as a condition there is consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With consciousness as a condition there is name & form."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With name & form as a condition there are the six sense spheres."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With the six sense spheres as a condition there is contact."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With contact as a condition there is feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With feeling as a condition there is craving."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With craving as a condition there is clinging/sustenance."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With clinging/sustenance as a condition there is becoming."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With becoming as a condition there is birth."}
{"label": 0, "text": "With birth as a condition, then old age & death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair come into play."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such is the origination of this entire mass of stress & suffering.Now from the remainderless fading & cessation of that very ignorance there is the cessation of fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of fabrications there is the cessation of consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of consciousness there is the cessation of name & form."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of name & form there is the cessation of the six sense spheres."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of the six sense spheres there is the cessation of contact."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of contact there is the cessation of feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of feeling there is the cessation of craving."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of craving there is the cessation of clinging/sustenance."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of clinging/sustenance there is the cessation of becoming."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of becoming there is the cessation of birth."}
{"label": 0, "text": "From the cessation of birth, then old age & death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair all cease."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such is the cessation of this entire mass of stress & suffering.This is the noble method that is rightly seen & rightly ferreted out by discernment."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Sariputta Now, the Blessed One has said, 'Whoever sees dependent co-arising sees the Dhamma; whoever sees the Dhamma sees dependent co-arising.'Sariputta"}
{"label": 0, "text": "First there is the knowledge of the steadfastness of the Dhamma (dependent co-arising), after which there is the knowledge of Unbinding."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Now what is becoming?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These three are becomings sensual becoming, form becoming, & formless becoming."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called becoming.becoming?And what is clinging/sustenance?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These four are clingings sensuality clinging, view clinging, precept & practice clinging, and doctrine of self clinging."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called clinging.clinging/sustenance?And what is craving?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These six are classes of craving craving for forms, craving for sounds, craving for smells, craving for tastes, craving for tactile sensations, craving for ideas."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called craving.craving?And what is feeling?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These six are classes of feeling feeling born from eye-contact, feeling born from ear-contact, feeling born from nose-contact, feeling born from tongue-contact, feeling born from body-contact, feeling born from intellect-contact."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called feeling.feeling?And what is contact?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These six are classes of contact eye-contact, ear-contact, nose-contact, tongue-contact, body-contact, intellect-contact."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called contact.contact?And what are the six sense spheres?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These six are sense spheres the eye-sphere, the ear-sphere, the nose-sphere, the tongue-sphere, the body-sphere, the intellect-sphere."}
{"label": 0, "text": "These are called the six sense spheres.the six sense spheres?And what is name & form?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Feeling, perception, intention, contact, & attention This is called name."}
{"label": 0, "text": "The four great elements, and the form dependent on the four great elements This is called form."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This name & this form are called name & form.name & form?And what is consciousness?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These six are classes of consciousness eye-consciousness, ear-consciousness, nose-consciousness, tongue-consciousness, body-consciousness, intellect-consciousness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is called consciousness.consciousness?And what are fabrications?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "These three are fabrications bodily fabrications, verbal fabrications, mental fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "These are called fabrications.fabrications?And what is ignorance?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Not knowing stress, not knowing the origination of stress, not knowing the cessation of stress, not knowing the way of practice leading to the cessation of stress This is called ignorance.ignorance?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The ending of the fermentations is for one who knows & sees, I tell you, not for one who does not know & see."}
{"label": 0, "text": "For one who knows what & sees what?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "'Such is form, such its origination, such its disappearance."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such is feeling."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such is perception."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such are fabrications."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Such is consciousness, such its origination, such its disappearance.' The ending of the fermentations is for one who knows in this way & sees in this way.The knowledge of ending in the presence of ending has its prerequisite, I tell you."}
{"label": 0, "text": "It is not without a prerequisite."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what is its prerequisite?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Release."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Release has its prerequisite, I tell you."}
{"label": 0, "text": "It is not without a prerequisite."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what is its prerequisite?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Dispassion."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Disenchantment."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Knowledge & vision of things as they actually are present."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Concentration."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Pleasure."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Serenity."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Rapture."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Joy."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Conviction."}
