{"label": 0, "text": "Monks, ignorance is the leader in the attainment of unskillful qualities, followed by lack of conscience & lack of concern."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In a unknowledgeable person, immersed in ignorance, wrong view arises."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong view, wrong resolve arises."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong resolve, wrong speech."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong speech, wrong action."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong action, wrong livelihood."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong livelihood, wrong effort."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong effort, wrong mindfulness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of wrong mindfulness, wrong concentration arises.Clear knowing is the leader in the attainment of skillful qualities, followed by conscience & concern."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In a knowledgeable person, immersed in clear knowing, right view arises."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right view, right resolve arises."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right resolve, right speech."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right speech, right action."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right action, right livelihood."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right livelihood, right effort."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right effort, right mindfulness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "In one of right mindfulness, right concentration arises."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Ven."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Ananda went to the Blessed One and, on arrival, having bowed down to the Blessed One, sat to one side."}
{"label": 0, "text": "As he was sitting there, Ven."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Ananda said to the Blessed One, This is half of the holy life, lord having admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues.Don't say that, Ananda."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Don't say that."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Having admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues is actually the whole of the holy life."}
{"label": 0, "text": "When a monk has admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues, he can be expected to develop & pursue the noble eightfold path.And how does a monk who has admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues, develop & pursue the noble eightfold path?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is the case where a monk develops right view dependent on seclusion, dependent on dispassion, dependent on cessation, resulting in relinquishment."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He develops right resolve ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right speech ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right action ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right livelihood ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right effort ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right mindfulness ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "right concentration dependent on seclusion, dependent on dispassion, dependent on cessation, resulting in relinquishment."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is how a monk who has admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues, develops & pursues the noble eightfold path.And through this line of reasoning one may know how having admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues is actually the whole of the holy life It is in dependence on me as an admirable friend that beings subject to birth have gained release from birth, that beings subject to aging have gained release from aging, that beings subject to death have gained release from death, that beings subject to sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair have gained release from sorrow, lamentation, pain, distress, & despair."}
{"label": 0, "text": "It is through this line of reasoning that one may know how having admirable people as friends, companions, & colleagues is actually the whole of the holy life."}
{"label": 0, "text": "More on Right View.And how is right view the forerunner?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "One discerns wrong view as wrong view."}
{"label": 0, "text": "One discerns right view as right view."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is one's right view."}
{"label": 0, "text": "And what is wrong view?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "'There is nothing given, nothing offered, nothing sacrificed."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is no fruit or result of good or bad actions."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is no this world, no next world, no mother, no father, no spontaneously reborn beings; no brahmans or contemplatives who, faring rightly & practicing rightly, proclaim this world & the next after having directly known & realized it for themselves.' This is wrong view.And what is right view?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "Right view, I tell you, is of two sorts There is right view with fermentations, siding with merit, resulting in the paraphernalia (of becoming); and there is noble right view, free from fermentations, transcendent, a factor of the path.And what is the right view that has fermentations, sides with merit, & results in paraphernalia?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "'There is what is given, what is offered, what is sacrificed."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There are fruits & results of good & bad actions."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is this world & the next world."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is mother & father."}
{"label": 0, "text": "There are spontaneously reborn beings; there are brahmans & contemplatives who, faring rightly & practicing rightly, proclaim this world & the next after having directly known & realized it for themselves.' This is the right view that has fermentations, sides with merit, & results in paraphernalia.And what is the right view that is free from fermentations, transcendent, a factor of the path?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "The discernment, the faculty of discernment, the strength of discernment, analysis of qualities as a factor for Awakening, the path factor of right view in one developing the noble path whose mind is noble, whose mind is free from fermentations, who is fully possessed of the noble path."}
{"label": 0, "text": "This is the right view that is free from fermentations, transcendent, a factor of the path.One tries to abandon wrong view & to enter into right view This is one's right effort."}
{"label": 0, "text": "One is mindful to abandon wrong view & to enter & remain in right view This is one's right mindfulness."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Thus these three qualities  right view, right effort, & right mindfulness  run & circle around right view."}
{"label": 0, "text": "More on Right Action & Right Speech.Having thus gone forth, following the training & way of life of the monks, abandoning the taking of life, he abstains from the taking of life."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He dwells with his rod laid down, his knife laid down, scrupulous, kind, compassionate for the welfare of all living beings."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Abandoning the taking of what is not given, he abstains from taking what is not given."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He takes only what is given, accepts only what is given, lives not by stealth but by means of a self that has become pure."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Abandoning uncelibacy, he lives a celibate life, aloof, refraining from the sexual act that is the villager's way."}
{"label": 0, "text": "More on Right Action & Right Speech for Lay People.Abandoning sensual misconduct, he abstains from sensual misconduct."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He does not get sexually involved with those who are protected by their mothers, their fathers, their brothers, their sisters, their relatives, or their Dhamma; those with husbands, those who entail punishments, or even those crowned with flowers by another man.Abandoning false speech, he abstains from false speech."}
{"label": 0, "text": "When he has been called to a town meeting, a group meeting, a gathering of his relatives, his guild, or of the royalty (i.e., a royal court proceeding), if he is asked as a witness, 'Come & tell, good man, what you know' If he doesn't know, he says, 'I don't know.' If he does know, he says, 'I know.' If he hasn't seen, he says, 'I haven't seen.' If he has seen, he says, 'I have seen.' Thus he doesn't consciously tell a lie for his own sake, for the sake of another, or for the sake of any reward."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Right Mindfulness.This is the direct path for the purification of beings, for the overcoming of sorrow & lamentation, for the disappearance of pain & distress, for the attainment of the right method, & for the realization of Unbinding  in other words, the four frames of reference."}
{"label": 0, "text": "What four?There is the case where a monk remains focused on the body in & of itself  ardent, alert, & mindful  putting aside greed & distress with reference to the world."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He remains focused on feelings."}
{"label": 0, "text": "mind."}
{"label": 0, "text": "mental qualities in & of themselves  ardent, alert, & mindful  putting aside greed & distress with reference to the world.BodyAnd how is does the monk remain focused on the body in & of itself?"}
{"label": 0, "text": "There is the case of a monk who, having gone to the wilderness, to the shade of a tree, or to an empty building, sits down folding his legs crosswise, holding his body erect and setting mindfulness to the fore [lit to the front of the chest]."}
{"label": 0, "text": "Always mindful, he breathes in; mindful he breathes out.Breathing in long, he discerns, 'I am breathing in long'; or breathing out long, he discerns, 'I am breathing out long.' Or breathing in short, he discerns, 'I am breathing in short'; or breathing out short, he discerns, 'I am breathing out short.' He trains himself, 'I will breathe in sensitive to the entire body.' He trains himself, 'I will breathe out sensitive to the entire body.' He trains himself, 'I will breathe in calming bodily fabrication.' He trains himself, 'I will breathe out calming bodily fabrication.' Just as a skilled turner or his apprentice, when making a long turn, discerns, 'I am making a long turn,' or when making a short turn discerns, 'I am making a short turn'; in the same way the monk, when breathing in long, discerns, 'I am breathing in long'; or breathing out long, he discerns, 'I am breathing out long' ."}
{"label": 0, "text": "He trains himself, 'I will breathe in calming bodily fabrication.' He trains himself, 'I will breathe out calming bodily fabrication.'Just asIn this way he remains focused internally on the body in & of itself, or externally on the body in & of itself, or both internally & externally on the body in & of itself."}
