{"label": 1, "text": "By the power defined in the preceding sutra, the inherent character, distinctive marks and conditions of beings and powers are made clear."}
{"label": 1, "text": "For through this power, as defined, we get a twofold view of each object, seeing at once all its individual characteristics and its essential character, species and genus; we see it in relation to itself, and in relation to the Eternal."}
{"label": 1, "text": "Thus we see a rose as that particular flower, with its colour and scent, its peculiar fold of each petal; but we also see in it the species, the family to which it belongs, with its relation to all plants, to all life, to Life itself."}
