{"label": 1, "text": "those which are active, and those which are not yet definable."}
{"label": 1, "text": "Every object has characteristics belonging to its past, its present and its future."}
{"label": 1, "text": "In a fir tree, for example, there are the stumps or scars of dead branches, which once represented its foremost growth; there are the branches with their needles spread out to the air; there are the buds at the end of each branch and twig, which carry the still closely packed needles which are the promise of the future."}
{"label": 1, "text": "In like manner, the chrysalis has, as its past, the caterpillar; as its future, the butterfly."}
{"label": 1, "text": "The man has, in his past, the animal; in his future, the angel."}
