{"label": 1, "text": "The man of desire wins from his works the reward of pleasure, or incurs the penalty of pain; or, as so often happens in life, his guerdon, like the passionate mood of the lover, is part pleasure and part pain."}
{"label": 1, "text": "Works done with self-seeking bear within them the seeds of future sorrow; conversely, according to the proverb, present pain is future gain."}
{"label": 1, "text": "But, for him who has gone beyond desire, whose desire is set on the Eternal, neither pain to be avoided nor pleasure to be gained inspires his work."}
{"label": 1, "text": "He fears no hell and desires no heaven."}
{"label": 1, "text": "His one desire is, to know the will of the Father and finish His work."}
{"label": 1, "text": "He comes directly in line with the divine Will, and works cleanly and immediately, without longing or fear."}
{"label": 1, "text": "His heart dwells in the Eternal; all his desires are set on the Eternal."}
