{"label": 1, "text": "The Three Potencies are the three manifested modifications of the one primal material, which stands opposite to perceiving consciousness."}
{"label": 1, "text": "These Three Potencies are called Substance, Force, Darkness; or viewed rather for their moral colouring, Goodness, Passion, Inertness."}
{"label": 1, "text": "Every material manifestation is a projection of substance into the empty space of darkness."}
{"label": 1, "text": "Every mental state is either good, or passional, or inert."}
{"label": 1, "text": "So, whether subjective or objective, latent or manifest, all things that present themselves to the perceiving consciousness are compounded of these three."}
